verbose_text: It was found that the amount of one of the forms of vitamin D-25 (OH) D3 in the serum at 30 ng/ml can inhibit the secretion of proinflammatory cytokines (IL-6 and TNF-alpha) induced by lipopolysaccharide (LPS), which is a component of bacterial walls [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
